Avanan is an enterprise AI-based cloud security platform that prevents phishing, malware, data leakage, account takeover, & shadow IT for full-suite cloud applications like Office 365. Avanan is the only solution that can fully secure your cloud email and communication, with a unique architecture built specifically for the cloud.
Avanan Splunk App allows to collect security events generated by the Avanan security platform, and perform actions on the collected events.

SETUP
- Enable Splunk integration in your Avanan Portal settings: go to Configuration > Security App Store > Splunk and select "Upload to the Avanan Splunk App". The Splunk App needs to be enabled before it can be configured.
- Contact Avanan Support to get API credentials - ClientId and ClientSecret.
- Deploy the Avanan Splunk App in your Splunk instance.
- Once the app is deployed the setup screen shows up. Enter there ClientId and ClientSecret on the setup page. Note that it is also possible to access setup page later by clicking the gear icon in the top left corner ("Manage Apps"), find the Avanan app and clicking "Set up" action.

USAGE
- Once fully configured, the security events will be collected to your Splunk instance.
- The App provides an "Open in Avanan" action for every event. To use it, open event details, and click "Actions" > "Open in Avanan". An Avanan browser tab will be opened, showing the security event details, where you can quickly quarantine the event.
